The following packages were salvaged from beads (the MIT license terms are
satisfied by retaining this notice). They provide ADLG's Dolt infrastructure:
embedded/owned/external Dolt SQL server management, the warm "proxied server"
daemon, and the version-control / remote / sync / federation operations. Import
paths were rewritten from github.com/steveyegge/beads to
github.com/endermalkoc/asdf, and dependencies on beads' issue domain were severed
(see the surgery notes below).

  internal/doltserver
  internal/storage/dbproxy            (+ pidfile, proxy, server, util)
  internal/storage/doltutil
  internal/remotecache
  internal/doltremote
  internal/config
  internal/configfile
  internal/debug
  internal/lockfile
  internal/atomicfile
  internal/storage                    (version-control contracts: version_control,
                                       versioned, remote, sync, federation,
                                       compaction, history_viewer)
  internal/storage/versioncontrolops  (Dolt branch/commit/merge/clone/gc/flatten/
                                       backup over a DBConn)
  internal/storage/kvkeys

Surgery applied when lifting the version-control tier:
  - internal/storage/storage.go is a local shim; beads' issue-domain Storage
    interface and internal/types were NOT lifted.
  - versioncontrolops was decoupled from beads' issueops: the two pure helpers it
    used (ValidateRef, IsNothingToCommitError) were relocated into
    versioncontrolops/refutil.go.
  - versioned.go, compaction.go, and history_viewer.go were genericized — beads'
    *types.Issue / IssueSnapshot / CompactionCandidate were replaced with opaque
    rows (map[string]any) and generic Node* types, and issueID became nodeID.
  - merge_slot.go was NOT lifted: its lock is implemented as a beads Issue and it
    drives the full issue Storage interface, so it is a domain feature rather than
    Dolt infrastructure.
